    <section class="py-12 border-b border-terminal-border" id="container">
      <h3 class="text-terminal-amber mb-6">### dependency container</h3>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-terminal-fg leading-relaxed">
        <p>Bind interfaces to implementations, resolve dependencies:</p>

        <code
          class="block bg-terminal-dim rounded p-3 text-terminal-fg text-xs"
        >
          // Explicit binding<br />
          $app-&gt;bind(PaymentGateway::class, StripeGateway::class);<br /><br
          />
          // Singleton (resolved once)<br />
          $app-&gt;singleton(Logger::class, FileLogger::class);<br /><br />
          // Auto-wiring (resolves constructor dependencies)<br />
          $controller = $app-&gt;make(UserController::class);
        </code>

        <p class="text-terminal-dim text-sm mt-4">
          Constructor parameters with class types are resolved from the
          container. Scalar parameters require defaults or explicit bindings.
          Use <code class="text-terminal-green">bind()</code> for transient instances
          and <code class="text-terminal-green">singleton()</code> for one shared
          instance across the request lifecycle.
        </p>
      </div>

