    <section class="py-12 border-b border-terminal-border" id="method-override">
      <h3 class="text-terminal-amber mb-6">### http method override</h3>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-terminal-fg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Browser forms only support GET and POST. Arc supports method spoofing:
        </p>

        <code
          class="block bg-terminal-dim rounded p-3 text-terminal-fg text-xs"
        >
          &lt;form method="POST" action="/users/1"&gt;<br />
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;input type="hidden" name="_method" value="PUT"&gt;<br
          />
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;input name="name" value="Updated"&gt;<br />
          &lt;/form&gt;
        </code>

        <p class="mt-3">
          Or via API header: <code class="text-terminal-green"
            >X-HTTP-Method-Override: PATCH</code
          >
        </p>

        <p class="text-terminal-dim text-sm mt-2">
          Only POST requests can be overridden to PUT, PATCH, or DELETE. Use <code
            class="text-terminal-green">getOriginalMethod()</code
          > to see the actual HTTP method.
        </p>
      </div>

